column5: feedback
The dashboard takes forever to load when I have more than 100 items. I end up just refreshing and hoping it works.
Love the new dark mode! It's so much easier on my eyes during late-night sessions.
I can't figure out how to export my data to CSV. Is that even possible?
The app crashed when I tried to upload a file larger than 50MB. Lost all my progress.
Would be great if I could set up recurring tasks with custom intervals instead of just daily/weekly.
The search bar doesn't find items if I misspell even one letter. Fuzzy search would help a lot.
I accidentally deleted a project and there's no way to recover it. Please add an undo or trash feature.
The onboarding tutorial was really helpful. I was up and running in 10 minutes.
Every time I switch between tabs my unsaved changes are lost. This is incredibly frustrating.
Can you add keyboard shortcuts? I hate having to reach for the mouse for every action.
The mobile version is basically unusable. Buttons overlap and text gets cut off.
I love how simple the interface is. No clutter just the tools I need.
Loading the dashboard is really slow especially in the morning. Takes 15+ seconds sometimes.
The notification emails come way too frequently. I'd like a daily digest option instead.
I tried to invite a teammate but the invite link expired before they could accept. Very short window.
Integration with Slack would be a game changer for my workflow.
The color coding for priorities is genius. Makes it so easy to scan my task list.
I keep getting logged out randomly every few hours. Have to re-enter my password each time.
Would love a calendar view for deadlines. The list view doesn't give me a sense of what's coming up.
The file upload silently fails for PDFs over 10MB. No error message at all just nothing happens.
Your API docs are excellent. Had my integration working in under an hour.
The drag and drop for reordering tasks is broken on Firefox. Works fine on Chrome though.
I wish there was a way to archive completed projects instead of deleting them.
Dashboard performance has gotten worse over the past month. Used to be snappy now it lags.
The template gallery is a great addition. Saved me a ton of setup time on my new project.
I can't change my email address in settings. The save button is grayed out.
Still having dashboard loading issues. It's been weeks now and no improvement.
Any plans for a native desktop app? The browser tab gets lost among everything else.
Found the CSV export! But it doesn't include custom fields which makes it useless for my reporting.
App crashed again on large file upload. This is the third time this week.
The new filter options are great but the UI for combining multiple filters is confusing.
Please add a bulk edit feature. Updating 50 tasks one by one is painful.
I accidentally deleted another project. Seriously need a recycle bin or undo.
The recent performance improvements are noticeable. App feels much faster this week.
Tab switching still loses my unsaved work. This bug has been open for months.
Keyboard shortcuts were added! Thank you! The Ctrl+K command palette is perfect.
Mobile app is still broken. Can't even scroll on the main page on my iPhone.
The simplicity is what keeps me here. Please don't bloat it with features nobody asked for.
Dashboard loads faster now but the chart rendering is still laggy with large datasets.
Still getting too many notification emails. The digest option would really help.
The team invite flow worked this time. But the permissions UI is unclear about what each role can do.
Just saw you added Slack integration! Works perfectly. Exactly what I needed.
Would be nice if the color coding was customizable. The default colors are hard to distinguish for colorblind users.
Random logouts are still happening. I've cleared cache and cookies already. Definitely a backend issue.
Calendar view would help me plan sprints. Right now I'm exporting to Google Calendar manually.
File upload errors are more descriptive now which is nice. But the 10MB limit is still too low for our use case.
The webhook support in the API is really well designed. Saves me from polling.
Firefox drag and drop is fixed! Thanks for the quick turnaround.
Project archiving would also help with the storage quota warnings I keep getting.
Dashboard is still slow for me. I have 500+ items and it takes 20 seconds to render the main view.
